8 offense which has not been pardoned, shall have restored the right
8
9 to possess any firearm or other weapon prohibited by subsection A of
9
10 this section, the right to apply for and carry a handgun, concealed
10
11 or unconcealed, pursuant to the provisions of the Oklahoma Self-
11
12 Defense Act or as otherwise permitted by law, and have the right to
12
13 perform the duties of a peace officer, gunsmith, and for firearms
13
14 repair any other profession that requires possession, carry, or
14
15 transportation of a firearm.
