16 C. 1. Any person who:
16
17 a. has previously been convicted of a nonviolent felony,
17
18 and
18
19 b. has completed the entirety of the sentence imposed for
19
20 the offense and has had no additional misdemeanor or
20
21 felony convictions or charges pending for a period of
21
22 five (5) years since the completion of the sentence,
22
23 shall have restored the right to possess, carry, or transport any
23
24 non-semi-automatic firearm, may apply for and carry a handgun,
24
